description: Here,we found malat-1 expression was abnormally increased in sle patients and predominantly expressed in human monocytes.Additionally,silencing malat-1 significantly reduced the expression of il-21 in primary monocytes of sle patients.Furthermore,malat-1 exerts its detrimental effects by regulating sirt1 signaling.
The increased neat1 expression may be a potential contributor to the  elevated production of a number of cytokines and chemokines in sle patients.
